10/16/84  kermit request: log

Syntax: log {path} {-control_args}


Function: Instructs kermit to start logging file transfer information
listing files sent/received to/from the microcomputer and whether the
transfer was successful.


Arguments:

path
   The name of the segment to be used for logging transactions.
   If no path is specified, logging is defaulted to the segment
   kermit.log.


Control arguments:
-extend
   If path is the name of an existing segment, the segment will be
   extended to include all subsequent log information.  This is the
   default.
-truncate, -tc
   truncate the log file, if it already exists.
   (Default is to extend it.)
